HEADWORD: Excern
<hw>Ex*cern"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>excernere</ets>. See <er>Excrete</er>.]</ety> <def>To excrete; to
throw off through the pores; <as>as, fluids are <ex>excerned</ex> in
perspiration</as>.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

